The paper deals with the weight distribution of a specific type of error-correcting code, the Hamming code, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of recursive formulas and exponential sum techniques suggests a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The study of error-correcting codes also has applications in cryptography (cs.CC) and signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the use of moment identities and exponential sums is a common technique in numerical analysis (cs.NA).
